@node main
@title "Visual 1.00 Copyright © 1995 by Christophe Vallee."

                                  VISUAL 1.00
                     Copyright © 1995 by Christophe Vallee.

   Visual is a program to catalog your picture directories. It displays
   small representants of the pictures,called thumbnails, and can
   launch an arexx script to make a graphic program generate these small
   pictures (some ImageFX scripts are provided in this archive), so this
   program does not generate thumbnails itself.
   
   Why did I write this program:
      * Some program like Visual exist but I wanted a fast-display 
        program. Visual displays the thumbnails very fast since thumbnails
        are small pictures in Ham8 mode and since the palette is the same
        for all the thumbnails
      * Some thumbnail programs are demo or limited version.

   Since I hate limited version of program, or program which pops up
   requesters all the time, this programm is not a limited version.

    @{" How does it work ?  " link "how"}
    @{" General             " link "general"}
    @{" ARexx Interface     " link "arexx"}
    @{" History             " link "history"}

   This version of visual requires AGA (thumbnails are in ham8 mode).
   
   If you use this program and find it useful, send me an email (I like
   to know if somebody uses my program) at  vallee@ensea.fr
   
   If you use it with another program than ImageFX, and you have done
   some ARexx script, please email them to me, I'd put them in the
   archive.

   This program may be copied and freely distributed via electronic media
   such as Mailboxes, Internet and Usenet, as long as the whole archive is
   distributed completely and this doc is included without any changes.

   You're not allowed to add any files to the archive, delete any files 
   to the archive or modify any of the files in the archive.
   
@endnode

@node how
@title "How does it work ?"

   Visual scans a directory and for each entry (directory or file), if
   it finds a file with the same name and with the extension '.ICN',
   it loads the picture and diplay it.
   The '.ICN' file are small IFF pictures in ham8 mode.
   If visual doesn't find a '.ICN' file for a file, it displays the
   the picture 'def_file' which is in a directory that you can
   specify in the preferences. For directory, it uses 'def_dir',
   for volume , 'def_volume' and for assign 'def_assign'

   In this archive there are some '.ICN' file of some pictures in the
   directory Examples.

   If you double click on a icone it lauches a program that you can
   specify in the preferences (I use MegaView which launch a program
   according to its type with the WhatIs.library)

   (MegaView was written by Hans-Jörg Frieden in 1993.)

@endnode

@node general

   The first menu:
      Change   : to specify a new directory with an ASL requester
      Parent   : to scan the parent directory or the volumes if the
                 directory is the root of a volume
      Volume   : to scan the volume list
      Update   : to re-read the directory
      Unselect : to unselect all the entries
      About    : to get informations
      Quit     : to quit
     
   The ARexx menu:
      Update all entries :
             select all the files that have not a '.ICN' file and launch
             the arexx program script
      Update selected entries :
             select the files that have not a '.ICN' file and that are
             already selected and launch the arexx script
      Create thumbnails for all entries :
             Select all the files and launch the arexx script
      Create thumbnails for selected entries :
             Selected all the files that are already selected and
             launch the arexx script
 
   The preference menu:
      General : display a general requester
      Ecran   : display the ASL screen mode requester
      Font    : display the ASL font requester to select the font
                of the name of the thumbnails
      SavePrefs : save the preferences in ENV:Visual.prefs and
               ENVARC:Visual.prefs
      Reload prefs: reload the preferences
      
   During the program, you can use the arrow keys to move.

   The preference requester:
      Show hidden file : if not selected, visual doesn't display
             file or directory that have the protect bit 'H'
             (The '.ICN' file must have the protect bit 'H' too otherwise
              the file will be display)
      Show parent : if selected, show a thumbnail for the parent directory

      Icn dir : directory where Visual searchs for the defaults thumbnails
            (def_file,def_dir,def_volume,def_assign)
      Command : the filename of the command that will be lauched if
             a file is double clicked
      Palette : the name of the palette file
      ARexx scrirpt : the name of the script to generate thumbnails
      Box width,height : width of the box which is diplay around the
                     thumbnails
      Icn width,height : width and height of the thumbnails
                   These numbers are only useful for an ARexx script
      
      
@endnode


@node arexx
@title "ARexx Interface"

To generate '.ICN' file, you can do it yourself with any graphic program
or with the arexx script.
In an ARexx script, you will have to use commands to control Visual and
your graphic program.
You will need to send command to Visual to get the name of the file
and to get the preference width , height and palette filename.

Some ImageFX script are provided in this archive. They work fine with
ImageFX 2.0 and certainly with ImageFX 1.5.

Visual accepts 6 commands.

CHECK

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Check

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Return information about the CANCEL gadget.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      Returns a result of 0 if the CANCEL gadget has not been pressed
      otherwise a result of 5
     
GETMAIN

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      GetMain

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Return information.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      Returns a string containing information, in the following format:

         "filename_of_the_palette" width height

GETSELECTED

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      GetSelected

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Return the name of the first FILE selected and if this file
      isn't on the Visual window, put it on the window.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      Returns a string containing the filename.


MESSAGE

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Message Text

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Display a message in the window of Visual.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Text@{uu}
         Text of the message.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

UNSELECT

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      UnSelect

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Unselect the first file selected.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

UPDATE

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      UnSelect

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Unselect the first file selected and reload its icone.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

